@node Introduction
    
 What's FindSmall ?
   => A file finder tool !
    

@endnode

@node Installation
   	
    Just copy FindSmall into your C: drawer!
  	
    Remember: 
   			Now,  It's  NO CASESENSITIVE
   			  
@endnode

@node Usage
    
Available OPTIONS:
    
 {PATH}  (needed): FindSmall RAM:
                   => Find ALL files into RAM:
   	
 MATCHNAME or N:   FindSmall RAM: MATCHNAME *.gif
                   (<=> FindSmall RAM: MATCHNAME *.gif)
                   (<=> FindSmall RAM: N *.gif)
                   (<=> FindSmall RAM: matchNamE=*.gif)				    
                   => Find ALL gifs files into RAM:
   	
 MAXSIZE or - :    FindSmall RAM:toto/ - 10000
                   (<=> FindSmall RAM:toto/ MAXSIZE 10000)
                   => Find ALL files of less than 10000 bytes into RAM:toto/
   					
 MINSIZE or + :    FindSmall RAM:toto/ + 10000
                   (<=> FindSmall RAM:toto/ MINSIZE 10000)
                   => Find ALL files of more than 10000 bytes into RAM:toto/	
  
 MATCHCOMMENT or N :   FindSmall RAM: MATCHCOMMENT *amiga*
                   => Find ALL  files into RAM: with 'AMIGA' in comment
 
 RECURSIVE or R :   directory recursive scan.
 RECURSIVELEVEL or L:   set the deep of recursive scan
 DEBUG or D     :   show more informations...
 
  
So, for options madmans:
 
 FindSmall HD5:Cache/ MATCHNAME *.jpg MATCHCOMMENT http* + 10000 - 50000 debug recursive l=20 noerror
 
@endnode

